# docs/private — operator-only runbook

Copy this file to `docs/private/README.md` (or any filename under
`docs/private/`) and fill in the specifics. Everything under
`docs/private/` is gitignored **except** this example. The actual
runbook never ships to GitHub.

Use this directory for:

- Exact public IPs of production boxes (also lives in `deploy/.env.local`)
- The real Lightning addresses you're hosting (`zap@yourdomain`, `personal@yourdomain`)
- The brand + personal npubs (hex or bech32)
- BTCPay store id, instance URL, webhook URL
- Linode Object Storage bucket names + region
- Exact Voltage node hostname + macaroon path
- Cloudflare Firewall rule names you maintain
- Any account / service info that's inconvenient to look up later

## Suggested file layout inside docs/private/

| File | Contents |
|---|---|
| `README.md`    | index + table of contents |
| `hosts.md`     | Box A/B/C public IPs, VPC IPs, hostnames, SSH one-liners |
| `identities.md`| brand + personal npubs + hex, which nsec file holds which |
| `lightning.md` | Voltage hostname, macaroon path, BTCPay store id, webhook secret rotation notes |
| `storage.md`   | Linode bucket names, Blossom mirror URLs, archive retention policy |
| `playbooks.md` | "when X breaks, do Y" — incident runbook |

## Discipline

- Never paste a **private key** (nsec, macaroon, access-key-secret) in
  here — those live only in `.env` files or on the relevant box. This
  directory is for *pointers* and *references*, not secrets.
- Keep a copy in 1Password / Bitwarden too — if the laptop dies,
  gitignored files die with it.
- Treat as append-only during normal work; do a tidy-up pass
  periodically so the runbook stays scannable.
